reviewText: An excellent example of "Film Noir" movies.

Tom Conway is sober and sharp, doing a silky smooth job in a Falcon type role. An example of the era in British mystery films, cheaply made but the stamp collecting subject matter is interesting. The sidekick named Barney is well-played and enjoyable. I love the long, extended sequences of  actual Lockheed Constellation aircraft landings, and the Jaguar auto in original condition. Early 50's nostalgia for fans of such things.
My dad liked this video, he is into old muder mystery movies and this was a great addition to his collection.
quality of the dvd could be better - but great seller AAAAA++++++++++
